s and runs on the JS backends (there a \"byte\" is a UTF-16 code unit — the\nJS-side encoding — which is correct for JS-hosted code).\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"The UTF-8 byte length. On wasm: the `StrLen` intrinsic (`array.len` on the `$Bytes`).\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[23,43],"name":"/tmp/7Xm5ns/purescript-wasm-base-v0.2.0/src/Wasm/String.purs","start":[23,1]},"title":"byteLength"},{"children":[],"comments":"The byte (0-255) at index `i`, **unchecked** (out of range traps). On wasm: the `StrByteAt`\nintrinsic (`array.get` on the `$Bytes`).\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[27,46],"name":"/tmp/7Xm5ns/purescript-wasm-base-v0.2.0/src/Wasm/String.purs","start":[27,1]},"title":"byteAt"},{"children":[],"comments":"Allocate a `String` of `n` **zeroed** bytes, to be filled with `unsafeSetByte`. On wasm: the\n`StrNew` intrinsic (a zeroed `$Str`).\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[31,42],"name":"/tmp/7Xm5ns/purescript-wasm-base-v0.2.0/src/Wasm/String.purs","start":[31,1]},"title":"unsafeNew"},{"children":[],"comments":"Write byte `b` (0-255) at index `i`, **mutating the string in place**, and return that same\nstring, so a builder loop threads it — keeping the write live (not dead-code-eliminated) and\nordered by the data dependency, without needing an effect. Unchecked (out of range traps). On\nwasm: the `StrSetByte` intrinsic (`array.set`, then yields the string).\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"String"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[37,63],"name":"/tmp/7Xm5ns/purescript-wasm-base-v0.2.0/src/Wasm/String.purs","start":[37,1]},"title":"unsafeSetByte"}],"name":"Wasm.String","reExports":[]}],"packageMeta":{"description":"a thin PureScript bridge to the low-level operations \nthe purs-wasm provides as intrinsics\n","homepage":"https://github.com/purs-wasm/purescript-wasm-base.git","license":["MIT"],"name":"purescript-wasm-base","repository":{"type":"git","url":"https://gi